.TH ELOT-EXPORTER 1 "APRIL 2026" "ELOT-Exporter 0.10.1"
.SH NAME
elot-exporter \- Export OWL ontologies to Org-mode format
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B elot\-exporter
[\fI-hvVF\fR] [\fI--debug\fR] [\fI-o\fR=\fIOUTPUT\fR] [\fI--tangle-target\fR=\fITANGLE_TARGET\fR] \fIONTOLOGY_PATH\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B elot-exporter
is a command-line tool that converts OWL ontologies into a structured Org-mode
format. It provides a human-readable representation of an OWL ontology,
specifically tailored for use within Emacs and the ELOT (Emacs Literate Ontology Tool)
ecosystem.
.PP
The tool generates nested Org-mode headlines representing class and property
hierarchies, and renders axioms using Manchester Syntax.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help message and exit.
.TP
.BI \-o ", " \-\-output "=\fIOUTPUT\fR"
Optional switch to specify an explicit output filename. If not provided,
the output is written to standard output.
.TP
.BI \-\-tangle\-target "=\fITANGLE_TARGET\fR"
The OMN tangle target filename (default: <ontology-local-name>.omn).
This determines the \fI:tangle\fR argument in the generated Org-mode
header.
.TP
.BI \-F ", " \-\-force
Force overwrite if the output file exists and has been edited since it was
generated by \fBelot-exporter\fR.
.TP
.BI \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Verbose mode. Use this to see ontology statistics and basic processing info.
.TP
.BI \-\-debug
Debug mode. Use this for detailed processing logs and full stack traces on error.
Equivalent to \fB\-vv\fR.
.TP
.BI \-V ", " \-\-version
Print version information and exit.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I ONTOLOGY_PATH
Path to the ontology file (e.g., .owl, .ttl, .omn, .rdf), or '\-' to read
from standard input.
.SH CHECKSUMS
The exporter includes a SHA-256 checksum in each generated Org-mode file to
detect manual modifications. The checksum is stored in a line starting with:
.PP
.RS
#+ELOT_EXPORTER_CHECKSUM:
.RE
.PP
When an output file already exists,
.B elot-exporter
verifies its integrity. If the file has been modified since it was generated
(i.e., the checksum does not match), the tool will refuse to overwrite it
unless the
.B \-\-force
option is used. This prevents accidental loss of manual edits made to the
exported Org-mode files.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
0
Success.
.TP
1
Failure (e.g., ontology loading error, unexpected exception).
.SH EXAMPLES
Export an OWL file to Org-mode:
.PP
.RS
.B elot\-exporter ontology.owl -o ontology.org
.RE
.PP
Read from standard input and write to a file with verbose output:
.PP
.RS
.B cat ontology.ttl | elot\-exporter -v - -o ontology.org
.RE
